"Opaque black pour from a bomber into a snifter finishes with a small khaki head.  Smells of heavy cinnamon and touch of coffee, notes of brown sugar and oak as it warms.  Taste was quite complex with a burst of cinnamon followed by molasses, vanilla, raisins, chocolate covered cherries, and hint of roast coffee.  Good weight in the mouth, really coating the tongue.   I really enjoyed this beer.  The cinnamon starts off overpowering, but fades and integrates better as it warms.  I think this is an outstanding beer, but I enjoyed the standard B-Bomb a bit more."
