"Overall, this is a couple of steps above the original version.  I really enjoy the unique cinnamon flavor.  This is highly recommended."
"Pours a very opaque dark brown. Nearly black. Half a finger of light brown head. Sticks to the glass some. Smell initially was straight used coffee grounds. That subsided to make room for some roasted malt, faint cinnamon/nutmeg, a touch of alcohol. Mild oak tannins and some baker's chocolate, too. Flavor is sweet chocolate, some mild roast/coffee, hint of some sweet fruit (cherry?), and a tinge of alcohol. Really nice beer. Mouthfeel is a nice medium mouthfeel with low carbonation. One of the better ""winter"" beers out there."
