"Served alongside Bourbon Abominable. Dark brown body with a small beige cap. Grandiose cinnamon aroma followed by bourbon and vanilla. Spice and booze. Brown sugar and bourbon. Hard to compare this to its counterpart, as they are vastly different. Coffee character is overshadowed. This is a showcase for cinnamon, and while the flavor is tasty, this is definitely best split a few ways. Yum."
