"Edit from 12/28/14.  Had this beer on tap at the Red Hot, and immediately realized I need to increase my original score.  On tap at the RH, and with some time to sit and contemplate this great beer, it was apparent just what a great beer this is.  The coffee and cinnamon seemed to blend in seamlessly with the base beer and the bourbon, giving the beer a wonderful coffee caramel, toffee nougat and milk dud flavor profile.  To no great surprise, this beer was incredibly popular at the Red Hot.  Even at $10 for an 11.5 ounce pour, they blew through their keg in less than a day.  This is just delicious stuff."
